                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z31p82x/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>He defined Judaism under four heads.</p>\n            <p>1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> A belief in One God</p>\n            <p>2<hi rend=\"sup\">nd</hi> Man was created in the image of God</p>\n            <p>3<hi rend=\"sup\">rd</hi> Since man was created in the image of God<lb/> he should\n                endeavor to walk in his ways &amp; imi-<lb/>tate his perfection.</p>\n            <p>4<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> The Coming Messiah. The <sic>fulfilment</sic> of the<lb/>\n                covenant would be the messianic period.<lb/> He denied a personal messiah said the\n                fulfill<lb/>-ment of the covenant would be the general<lb/> perfection of\n                mankind—nay the complete re-<lb/>generation of man—when all the world would<lb/>\n                embrace Judaism believe in but One God<lb/> and have but one Religion. In a\n                word<lb/> that the Jews were to be the messiahs as they<lb/> were <del>the</del> a\n                nation of priests they would in<lb/> the fullness of time bring all mankind to<lb/>\n                their belief and thus redeem the world<lb/> &amp;c &amp;c in the same train.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Both the congregations here being orthodox<lb/>\n                <del>here</del> took many exceptions as you may sup<lb/>-pose to his remarks—nay I\n                think it safe<lb/> to say—the mass differed widely with<lb/> him—but that would not\n                signify much<lb/> perhaps, <hi rend=\"underline\">considering</hi> the <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">components</hi> of the <hi rend=\"underline\">mass</hi><lb/>\n                However I heard a number of highly intelli<lb/>-gent Jews express their dissent in\n                terms</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z31p82x/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
