                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z31p82x/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>not at all complimentary to the Rev Dr.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">He made little or no impression other<lb/> than by his presence\n                securing additional<lb/>\n                <sic>subscrition</sic> to the Israelite and collecting<lb/> from delinquents—in both\n                of which I learn<lb/> he was quite successful. You know the<lb/> object of his visit\n                to <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>—from there<lb/> he goes to <placeName>N.\n                    Y.</placeName> to attend the <date>August</date> meeting<lb/> of the Con G.\n                Lodge JOBB.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am devoting much of<lb/> my leisure to the study of our history\n                and religion<lb/> limited indeed are the sources from whence<lb/> I can derive the\n                information my mind seeks<lb/> my thirst craves. I realize fully the value<lb/> of\n                your opening editorial Vol V No 1. “De-<lb/>mand for Education.” the Mishna\n                Talmud<lb/> and Posekin<add>?</add> are indeed sealed books to<lb/> me. I would\n                study the Chaldaic tongue<lb/> but can find no teacher and being but an\n                in<lb/>different Hebrew Scholar I make little<lb/> progress. However I do not\n                despair. The Pen<lb/>-tatuech and Prophets are the source of<lb/> unalloyed\n                enjoyment though I often very<lb/> often am at a loss and pray for a\n                commenta<lb/>-tor. I trust you will be able to dis-<lb/>-cuss the question\n                propounded in my letter<lb/> of the <date>9<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> in your\n                    <date>October</date> number I shall</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z31p82x/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
